    "recap_headline": "Sacred Heart",
    "recap_text": "West Haven, Conn. \u2013\nSacred Heart baseball notched four doubles but fell short in a 4-2 loss to Yale.\nYale scored a run in each of the first two innings to take an early lead Tuesday afternoon.\nSacred Heart's pitching staff settled in from there, highlighted by\nWill Saxenmeyer\nstriking out the final batter of the third inning on three pitches.\nIn the fifth,\nChuck Tallman\ndoubled to left field, while Schueller recorded two strikeouts in the bottom half of the inning to keep the Bulldogs off the board.\nThe Pioneers continued to threaten at the plate, with\nWill Rudolph\ndoubling in the sixth inning, but Yale extended its lead in the bottom of the frame with a two-run home run.\nSacred Heart broke through in the eighth when\nRonan Donohue\ndoubled and later scored on a wild pitch. On the mound,\nAndrew Sager\nstruck out back-to-back batters in the bottom of the eighth to keep the Pioneers within reach.\nIn the ninth,\nKyle Cincinnati\ndoubled and later came around to score, but Sacred Heart could not complete the comeback as Yale held on for the 4-2 win.\nTop Performers\nRonan Donohue\n: 1-5, R, RBI, double, 2 A\nKyle Cincinnati\n: 1-1, R, double, 2 PO\nChuck Tallman\n: 2-4, double, 5 PO, 1 A\nWill Rudolph\n: 1-3, double, 1 PO\nWill Saxenmeyer\n: 2.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 2 SO\nJase Schueller\n: 1.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 2 SO\nAndrew Sager\n: 1.0 IP, 0 H, 0 R, 2 SO\nUp Next\nThe Pioneers travel to Quinnipiac this weekend, March 13-15, with first pitch set for 3 p.m. Friday and 1 p.m. Saturday and Sunday."
